rComments: You need to go to class to do well. This was her first time teaching and it showed during the first half of the class as most of the class failed the midterm and first paper. She made some adjustments for the second half and it was far better. This class does require a lot of work, probably the most work I put into any class in my 4 years.

Amazing prof! Lectures were very interesting and engaging. Students expected this to be a bird course which is why there's a lot of trash talk about the professor. Just put the same amount of effort/work you would in any average course and you should be fine.

although i ended up doing well in the course, this was one of the most unenjoyable experiences of my university career. She seemed to take it really personally when people didn't participate at her will or didn't do the readings, even lashing out in a kind of passive aggressiveness that you only see from someone youre in a relationship with

Although my grades were decent for this course, I have put more into this class than any other course I have taken in my undergrad. Amanda was adamant about changing the bird course reputation that this course once held. Lots of readings and a very long and time consuming group project. But what I disliked most was Amanda's arrogant attitude.

Easy A and considering the high class average, I wasn't alone. Prof posted all notes/assignment grading schemes/test material. She even mentioned several times how important certain slides where and sure enough they showed up on the test. Would recommend.

If you enjoy kind, respectful, inspiring professors and courses, spare yourself and dont take this class. Massive group projects, and tough exams. Please ignore the wonderful legacy this course used to have as Amanda has ruined it. Went from being an easy A with Dr. Orlick to one of the hardest and labour-intensive courses Ive ever enrolled in.

I would give Amanda a 0 if I could. Horrendous prof with the toughest marking scheme. Instead of not giving marks on a section of a project, she takes away marks from your total. Gives an unrealistic amount of readings, and if you don't do them she will yell at the class. It was apparent that the role of teaching a class went to her head.

Amanda is a stern but fair, first time prof. She has a grading rubric for each assignment and as long as you follow that to a T, you end up with an 'A'. Tests were made up of fill in the blanks, multiple choice, short/long answer based off key points in her slides, which are posted. Easy A so far...

Her teaching style and attitude towards students turned this course from something to look forward to into something to dread. Very passive aggressive and yells at the class. First time teaching and it was evident. This PhD candidate was the toughest marker Ive ever had at the university. It seems as though she wants her students to fail. Avoid.
If you want a good grade read all of the instructions on assignments and exams carefully.
Super kind prof. She really cares about her students and is willing to admit when she made mistakes. Just show up, study the powerpoint slides, and read the instructions for an A.

Small individual assignment, group assignment, and a couple of exams. She gave lots of hints about the type of exam questions and what she expected on assignments during lectures. Relatively tough grader, but as long as you read all instructions carefully you will do great.

This was Amanda's first time teaching this course. It is obvious she cares about the content and her students. She provides a lot of feedback on assignments and was always available via email. There was no textbook and the articles assigned were generally quite short. Overall, great prof and pretty great course.

She expects way to much of her students. Not only does she expect her student to ready 203 articles before every class but also to basically write a PHD paper for the final assignment. She trying to improves someone quality of life but after every class my quality of life seems to decrease

The first time I have failed a midterm in my entire undergrad, I am a 75-80 percent student in every single class taken but somehow managed to get a 47 on her midterm after studying like I would/did for every single other class. Instead of just not giving you marks on assignments she deducts extra ones off. Do yourself a favor and never take this
You have to do the readings and go to class or you have no chance at passing. Even then it's ify...

Definitely the worst professor (and I use the term "professor" loosely) I have ever had. It is evident the power of teaching a course got to her head, as she was condescending and frequently passive aggressive/ sarcastic in her interactions with the class. Her marking scheme is unclear and she sets students up to fail. Avoid her at all costs!!!

This class was supposed to inspire, and improve our quality of life. Instead, it encompassed misery, and featured the occasional outburst when things did not go her way. This PhD candidate should not be able to be in another position of power where said power can be abused.

Quality of life has always been a highly anticipated course for many 4th year students, as it has been taught by the kind, and inspirational Terry Orlick. A course, which should have been a positive highlight of my undergraduate career, turned out to be the biggest disappointment in all my four years at uOttawa as a result of this PhD candidate.

Amanda is suppose to be improving my quality of life and somehow has made me hate this class. She is so demanding and yells at you for not having done the readings. Her expectations on assignments are unclear and will penalize you for everything. This by far has been the worst class I've taken!!! Toughest Grader ever!!! Avoid classes with her!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: It's pretty terrible and ironic that the class is about methods to improve the quality of life of individuals when it is sucking the life out of us. I have taken some pretty awful classes but this by far takes the prize and runs with it. Job well done for keeping students busy working in groups so that 3 hours per week of class time is justified.

The worst prof Ive ever had. This class is by far the biggest disappointment of my undergrad. Made what should be an easy course unnecessarily difficult, and has unclear expectations for assignments. Unless you enjoy low marks and a prof who is passive aggressive avoid this class and avoid her. She should probably just stick to research.

This prof is unclear with her expectations and makes class very boring. I am a straight A student, and struggle to get Bs in this class. The class is unclear, very theory heavy, and full of busy work. The prof has tried to make this easy class aggressively hard, and over did herself. Horrible class and prof

This course is supposed to be an easy A, however Amanda has managed to make this course one of the hardest to succeed in as well as unenjoyable. This course is no longer about happiness, but about class participation assignments every lecture and impossible assignments. She has high expectations and is way too energetic. It has decreased my QOL.

Overall I found this professor to be quite unprofessional. Although it is her first time teaching, throughout the semester she was passive aggressive to the class when we didnt answer questions, even yelling at us one time. The assignment was horrendously organized with unclear expectation.

New prof. This class used to be an easy A+ but not anymore. Lots of readings, yells at the class if you don't do them or don't answer her questions. Unclear expectations for assignments. The course is about improving quality of life and ironically, she somehow managed to decrease mine.
